The TRLS is designed to be carried by those responding to Active Shooter situations and deployed immediately once the threat is neutralized and security is set. It does have various patches on the interior as well as a graphic on the back lining (see close-up photos). It has a leather patch applied to the exterior that reads "Avirex Ltd". The lining is printed with a Certificate of Service given to Charles T Reilly and signed by Bill Halsey. The jacket has two large pockets affixed to the front that can be accessed either from the top by unbuttoning the flap, or from the side.  The back has a double flap at the top, dropped sleeves and the armpits have gusseted extensions for ease of movement.  -US Navy pattern -Bi-swing back -Genuine lamb’s wool shearling mouton fur collar like the WWII era.  The fur collar is removable. -Knit cuffs and waistband -Top entry front flap pockets -Full zip with front wind flap -Under arm grommets  She Paid $550 and I am selling for $250
